header.gameNote: NEW YORK LIFE ACC MEN'S TOURNAMENT - QUARTERFINAL

videos.description: Seventh Woods gets the tough layup to give UNC its first bucket after starting 0-for-11 from the field.
videos.headline: Woods makes and-1 layup to end UNC's drought

videos.description: Seventh Woods finds Sterling Manley with a nice outlet pass for the dunk.
videos.headline: Manley with the fast-break slam

videos.description: Lonnie Walker IV makes a nice backdoor cut and gets to the hoop for the easy dunk.
videos.headline: Miami's Walker throws it down

videos.description: Miami coach Jim Larranaga wants his team to stop making uncharacteristic mistakes and calm down in the second half.
videos.headline: Larranaga says Miami made too many mistakes in first half

videos.description: Joel Berry comes down on another player's foot and rolls his ankle, would return to the game.
videos.headline: Berry rolls his ankle

videos.description: Miami's Ja'Quan Newton drains the deep shot with the shot clock ticking down
videos.headline: Newton hits the step-back jumper

videos.description: UNC's Theo Pinson uses a nice crossover to get by the defender and scoops it high off the glass.
videos.headline: Pinson shows off old-school moves

videos.description: Theo Pinson runs down the floor and dunks home a monstrous two-handed slam.
videos.headline: Pinson goes down main street for thunderous slam

videos.description: Theo Pinson drops 25 points and 11 boards to lead the Tar Heels in to the ACC semifinals against bitter rival Duke.
videos.headline: Pinson credits bench and jokes about his 'beautiful bed'
